Famous Brands has sold its controlling 51 percent which it bought in 2008 back to the Sideris family. JOHANNESBURG- Boutique café group Tashas is back in the hands of its founders. Famous Brands has sold its controlling 51 percent - which it bought in 2008 - back to the Sideris family. The family held the remaining 49 percent. READ: Famous Brands' share price takes a hit Famous Brands says the sale is in line with its three-year strategic road map. That includes a narrower focus of investment of resources in the Signature brands portfolio. It says flexing brands like Wimpy, FEGO and Mugg & Bean performed well during the lockdown because they were allowed to operate. However, Famous Brands says its signature portfolio is likely to be consolidated, with a focus on brands that show the best opportunity for scale.